b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe15085.htm)  [Next](sbe15087.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B002DEMBWG/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_The Upanishads, Part 2 (SBE15)_ , by Max Muller, [1879], at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 193\n\n### EIGHTH BR\xc3\x82HMA _N_ A.\n\n1\\. Let him meditate on speech as a cow. Her four udders are the words Svaha,\nVasha _t_ , Hanta, and Svadha 1. The gods live on two of her udders, the Svaha\nand the Vasha _t_ , men on the Hanta, the fathers on the Svadha. The bull of\nthat cow is breath (pra _n_ a), the calf the mind.\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[193:1](sbe15086.htm#fr_563) There are two udders, the Svaha and Vasha _t_ ,\non which the gods feed, i.e. words with which oblations are given to the gods.\nWith Hanta they are given to men, with Svadha to the fathers.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: V, 9](sbe15087.htm)\n\n'